It has been my experience that one who denies God is limited to his/her own physical and mental resources, which are generally easily overwhelmed or exhausted in the clutch of adversity.<br>
Denouncement of God or failure to recognize that He exists is, in my estimation, a statement from someone who is so weak and insecure that they must declare their strengths and wisdom as products of their own doing.  Denial is the ability to lie to oneself.  Denial of God is the ability to lie with greater fecundity to the entire creation.<br><br>
